					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616316#post-1688609</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616316/scp-1727#post-1688609</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 Jan 2013 01:41:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>FullHazard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>322120</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Or any number of a thousand other alien psychologies that a sentient building may have.</p> <p>Three examples<br /> 1: It is a machine. It doesn't view what it does as a business, it is its job, the way a machine might view a job: what it was designed to do. It does what it is supposed to do, regardless of how self-destructive they may be. It is like that sentient nuke article, where the bomb feels the need to explode despite the fact that that would destroy it, because that is what nukes are made for.<br /> 2: It is not trying to maximize its profits. It is a machine. It doesn't need money.<br /> 3: It could be assuming that people who push the special button know what's in store. It might not know that this isn't standard in the world, to have sapient car washes that have a 'hurl me to my death' button. If somebody gives you money to kill them, then, you can't argue that killing them would be bad for business. It might think that not killing people who push the magic button will get the survivors to complain to the government for fraud and false advertising.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
